This paper deals with the task of identifying users based on their behavioral patterns, which is a common problem in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of data sets such as call data records, web browsing histories, and GPS trajectories, which are typically studied in the fields of data mining and machine learning (cs.SI, cs.DB). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of $k$-anonymization in resisting user identification attacks, which is a topic of interest in the field of cryptography (cs.CY). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of different algorithms for user identification, which is a problem in the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
